cs.DC, cs.LO, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.NI. 

The paper deals with distributed computing models and their relationship with local algorithms. Therefore, cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves logic and theoretical computer science, which suggests cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.IT (Information Theory) as likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses infinite networks, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture).
